    • Enum Constant Detail

      • NULL

        public static final ReferenceExpression.ReferenceKind NULL
        The "null" reference. This is a reference value that can never be dereferenced. Similar to C's NULL pointer.

      • IDENTITY

        public static final ReferenceExpression.ReferenceKind IDENTITY
        The identity reference. This is the reference that when applied to any value v, returns a reference to v.

      • ARRAY_ELEMENT

        public static final ReferenceExpression.ReferenceKind ARRAY_ELEMENT
        An array element of reference. A reference of this kind is an instance of ArrayElementReference. It includes a reference to the "parent" array and an index.

      • TUPLE_COMPONENT

        public static final ReferenceExpression.ReferenceKind TUPLE_COMPONENT
        A tuple component reference. A reference of this kind is an instance of TupleComponentReference. It includes a reference to the "parent" tuple value and a concrete integer field index.

      • UNION_MEMBER

        public static final ReferenceExpression.ReferenceKind UNION_MEMBER
        A union member reference. A reference of this kind is an instance of UnionMemberReference. It includes a reference to the "parent" union value and an integer member index.

      • OFFSET

        public static final ReferenceExpression.ReferenceKind OFFSET
        An offset reference. A reference of this kind is an instance of OffsetReference. It includes a reference to a "parent" value and an integer "offset".
